Citation.sTitle: Dew points of pure DBN and DBU and vapor-liquid equilibria of water + DBN and water + DBU systems for cellulose solvent recycling
Citation.sAbstract: Dew points of pure 1,5-diazabicyclo[4.3.0]non-5-ene (DBN) and 1,8-diazabicyclo[5.4.0]undec-7-ene(DBU) were measured using low pressure distillation. The distillation experiments were conducted withina 0.5 - 12.1 kPa pressure range. The measured dew point data were in good agreement with the vaporpressure data available in the open literature. The combined measured dew point and literature vaporpressure data were modeled using an Antoine type equation.Vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) of water + DBN and water + DBU systems were measured using two variations of a static total pressure method. The VLE measurements were conducted within a 313 - 353 K temperature range. The results indicate a negative deviation from Raoult's law for both systems. Legendre polynomial and NRTL activity coefficient models were used to describe the liquid phases of the systems.
